cs.LO, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.PL, cs.DC 

The paper deals with the enforcement of opacity properties in discrete-event systems, which is a topic related to formal methods and verification (cs.LO). The paper also considers the presence of multiple intruders and their coordination, which is a topic related to security and cryptography (cs.CR). The proposed enforcement mechanisms involve the manipulation of system outputs, which is a topic related to control systems (cs.SY) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper deals with the decentralized enforcement of opacity, which is a topic related to distributed computing (cs.DC).
